<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>About - Library Management System</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link href="/styles/sample.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('./partials/header.ejs') %>

  <div class="container mt-5">
    <div class="text-center mb-4">
      <h1 class="fw-bold">📖 About Our Library Management System</h1>
      <p class="text-muted">Discover how we simplify book borrowing and showcase collections beautifully.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="row align-items-center">
      <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1524995997946-a1c2e315a42f" alt="Library" class="img-fluid rounded shadow">
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <h3>What is this Project?</h3>
        <p>
          Our Library Management System is a modern web application designed to streamline how books are showcased and borrowed in a digital library. With features like animated book cards, real-time search, and smooth flip-card interactions, it provides both functionality and a great user experience.
        </p>

        <h4>🔍 Features</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Interactive book showcase with hover animations and card flipping</li>
          <li>Borrowing form embedded within the book card for easy access</li>
          <li>Live search by title or author</li>
          <li>Clean and responsive UI with Bootstrap 5</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>🛠️ Technologies Used</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Node.js + Express.js (Server-side)</li>
          <li>EJS Templates</li>
          <li>Bootstrap 5 + Custom CSS</li>
          <li>Open Library API for book covers</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-5">
      <h4>👨‍💻 Developer Notes</h4>
      <p>
        This project was built to learn how to integrate frontend animations with backend form handling, while managing book data efficiently. It's lightweight, fast, and focused on improving the user experience.
      </p>
      <p>
        We aim to continue improving this system by adding features like login/authentication, book return tracking, and administrative controls.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%- include('./partials/footer.ejs') %>
</body>
</html>
